description:
One Month after India's WORST ever single aircraft disaster in her history - there are no clear answers / only smoke. Forget regular press conferences - it took the Govt 10 days to announce a death toll.
Worse - new exclusive reporting by Reuters shows that Air India was  operating in a dangerous manner - without conducting all the required checks on time.

Further Reading

comments.text:
Don't know why we all saw people kept blaming Boeing for the faults. But isn't Air India (Air Tata) and the Tata group the actual culprits here.


Boeing is a manufacturer and the corporation who bought their planes are responsible for spending for regular maintenance. If I'm the manufacturer and the client doesn't pay me for repairs do I owe them free repairs. On the other hand if the sales agreement say that Boeing should provide regular maintenance services (free or paid) they should also be held liable for the disaster.
